It’s true that it helped us a lot to connect with famous singers and also work actively to promote the group.
We come to the conclusion that work that is not seen is as if it does not exist.
Thanks to the help of the European Union, we can also afford quality teaching, equipment, etc.
Did you intend to go that far with The Tap Tap?
From the beginning I saw the potential that there was, that you can do something else.
The entertainment world is full of things that resemble each other.
Logically, in its own way, everything new is accepted with caution and takes a long time to accept.
There are few extraordinary things, but I dare say The Tap Tap is one of them.
The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly compassion, it is a natural reaction...
But compassion is totally superfluous because people with disabilities are not abandoned beings who suffer and from whom we should have compassion.
There are people who are able to live a full life and develop, provided, of course, that they have the necessary means.
I always say that if something goes well for people with disabilities, then it’s not just an advance for them, but for the whole society.
Did the fact that you are a demanding boss help, as many people describe you?
